  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fractures just below the hip often are treated with a so called Gliding Screw and Plate
      (DHS). Recently a new additional plate called a Trochanter Support Plate (TSP) which attaches
      to the DHS has become available which is claimed to give extra support to the fracture. In a
      prospective randomised study we wish to test the hypothesis that the TSP does not give any
      additional stability to the fracture treated with the DHS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
